
George takes a glance over at me. He starts the engine and stares at the road.
"What's your name?" He asks as he turns left on the street.
"Madeline," I stare at the road, not wanting to make eye contact with George. Just looking at him scares me and thinking that he's trying to be friendly scares me even more.
"I'm George. About the date, Madeline, I'm thinking dress casual, how you do everyday. It's not a big date anyways." He shrugs.
"But you'll have fun. I'm sure." Have fun with someone like him, never.
I feel like saying something but fearing my voice will crack I prefer to stay quiet.
"Be ready by seven." George didn't even look at me as we pulled up in my driveway. "I'll be waiting,"